          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="gk-num">1</td>
              <td>National Animal</td>
              <td><strong>Bengal Tiger</strong></td>
              <td>Panthera tigris tigris</td>
              <td>Declared under Project Tiger, 1973. Previously the Lion was the national animal.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="gk-num">2</td>
              <td>National Bird</td>
              <td><strong>Indian Peacock</strong></td>
              <td>Pavo cristatus</td>
              <td>Designated 1963. National bird of India since 26 Jan 1963.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="gk-num">3</td>
              <td>National Flower</td>
              <td><strong>Lotus</strong></td>
              <td>Nelumbo nucifera</td>
              <td>Sacred in Hindu and Buddhist traditions. Also the flower of goddess Lakshmi.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="gk-num">4</td>
              <td>National Fruit</td>
              <td><strong>Mango</strong></td>
              <td>Mangifera indica</td>
              <td>Called "King of Fruits". Cultivated in India for over 5,000 years.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="gk-num">5</td>
              <td>National Tree</td>
              <td><strong>Indian Banyan</strong></td>
              <td>Ficus benghalensis</td>
              <td>Also called "Kalpavriksha" (wish-fulfilling tree). Symbolises immortality.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="gk-num">6</td>
              <td>National River</td>
              <td><strong>Ganga</strong></td>
              <td>—</td>
              <td>Declared National River in 2008. Flows ~2,525 km within India.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="gk-num">7</td>
              <td>National Aquatic Animal</td>
              <td><strong>Gangetic Dolphin</strong></td>
              <td>Platanista gangetica</td>
              <td>Designated 5 October 2009. Freshwater dolphin; blind; found in Ganga-Brahmaputra system.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="gk-num">8</td>
              <td>National Heritage Animal</td>
              <td><strong>Indian Elephant</strong></td>
              <td>Elephas maximus indicus</td>
              <td>Designated 22 October 2010. Project Elephant launched 1992.</td>
            </tr>
